# {{ site.brandName }} — Small Business Valuation Data

> {{ site.brandName }} publishes SDE multiples and revenue multiples for {{ industries.all | length }} small business industries across 12 categories, derived from BizBuySell closed transaction data (CoStar Group). All valuations use a deterministic model: adjusted SDE × industry-specific multiple = baseline valuation range. Deal-readiness factors (revenue trend, owner involvement, customer concentration) apply a ±0.25–0.30× adjustment to the base multiple.

## Calculator

The free business valuation calculator is at {{ site.url }}/. It accepts six inputs:
industry category, annual SDE, annual revenue, revenue trend (declining / flat / growing 10–20% / growing 20%+), owner involvement level (high / moderate / low), and customer concentration (concentrated / diverse). It outputs a valuation range and a what-if simulation.

No email or registration required. Results are computed in the browser — no server round-trip.

## Adjustment Model

Adjustments to the industry median multiple:

- Revenue trend growing 20%+: +0.30× to both low and high multiple
- Revenue trend growing 10–20%: +0.15×
- Revenue trend flat: 0×
- Revenue trend declining: −0.25×
- Owner involvement low (systematized): +0.20×
- Owner involvement moderate: 0×
- Owner involvement high (owner-dependent): −0.20×
- Customer concentration diverse (no customer >15%): +0.10×
- Customer concentration concentrated (one customer ≥40%): −0.25×

Floor: no result below 1.0× SDE. Results rounded to nearest $5,000.

## Data Source

All industry multiples are derived from BizBuySell transaction records (CoStar Group).
Dataset: {{ site.transactionCount }}+ closed small business sales from Q1 {{ site.dataCoverageStart }} through Q4 {{ site.dataCoverageEnd }}.
